headline: 2 Cash-Producing Stocks on Our Watchlist and 1 to Steer Clear Of
summary: A company that generates cash isn’t automatically a winner. Some businesses stockpile cash but fail to reinvest wisely, limiting their ability to expand.

headline: Kimberly-Clark (KMB): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Since December 2024, Kimberly-Clark has been in a holding pattern, posting a small loss of 3.7% while floating around $128.23.
